Travelers at a German airport can now receive spiritual solace by entering a booth and listening to a prayer of their choice before boarding a plane. JOHANNESBURG - Travellers at a German airport can now receive spiritual solace by entering a booth and listening to a prayer of their choice before boarding a plane.The prayer booth at Stuttgart Airport's Terminal 3 features 300 prayers from various religions in 65 different languages.The 'Gebetomat', which roughly translates as 'pray-o-matic,' was first designed in 2008.